OL,3,CBritish rivers at risk of becoming
OL,4,C'dead zones' due to chicken pollution
OL,6,FHigh phosphate levels have been blamed
OL,7,Fas the leading cause of dead zones in
OL,8,Fthe River Wye, where manure runoff
OL,9,Ffrom a quarter of the UK's chickens
OL,10,Ffeeds into.
OL,12,FTom Tibbets used to swim in the river
OL,13,F20 years ago and now says it's
OL,14,Fbecoming too polluted.
OL,16,F"That amount of phosphorous there in
OL,17,Fthe water today won't necessarily be
OL,18,Fkilling something right now, but it's
OL,19,Fthis accumulation of nutrient in the
OL,20,Friver that will create blooms," he
OL,21,Ftold ITV News.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/8
