OL,3,CBritish rivers at risk of becoming
OL,4,C'dead zones' due to chicken pollution
OL,6,FThe research was also published
OL,7,Falongside a new opinion poll, which
OL,8,Fshowed 80% of people in Britain
OL,9,Funderestimate the proportion of
OL,10,Fchickens that are factory farmed.
OL,12,FOnly one in five people realise nearly
OL,13,Fall - more than 90% - of meat chickens
OL,14,Fare factory farmed and only 15% of
OL,15,Fpeople are aware farming is the
OL,16,Fbiggest polluter of UK rivers.
OL,18,FDespite this lack of awareness, 75%
OL,19,Fwould be willing to eat less chicken
OL,20,Fif it meant cleaner UK rivers and less
OL,21,Fenvironmental destruction overseas.
